"title": "1656: numbers, combinations",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1656: numbers, combinations",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Numbers may be combined for making a comparison. When they are combined in such a pattern as “two or three” the emphasis usually falls on the second figure.</p>\n<h2>Two and three</h2>\n<h3>Two or three witnesses</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut19:15\">DEU 19:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num35:30\">NUM 35:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut17:6\">DEU 17:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:16\">MAT 18:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor13:1\">2CO 13:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:19\">1TI 5:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:28\">HEB 10:28</a></p>\n<h3>Two or three as a small approximate number</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:20\">MAT 18:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs9:32\">2KI 9:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa17:6\">ISA 17:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos6:2\">HOS 6:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:27\">1CO 14:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:29\">1CO 14:29</a></p>\n<h3>Two and three in a climactic pattern</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl4:12\">ECC 4:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:15\">PRO 30:15</a></p>\n<h2>Three and four</h2>\n<h3>Three or four as a small approximate number</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer36:23\">JER 36:23</a></p>\n<h3>Three and four in a climactic pattern</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:18-Prov30:19\">PRO 30:18–30:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:15-Prov30:16\">PRO 30:15–30:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:21-Prov30:23\">PRO 30:21–30:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:29-Prov30:31\">PRO 30:29–30:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:3\">AMO 1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:6\">AMO 1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:9\">AMO 1:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:11\">AMO 1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:13\">AMO 1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos2:1\">AMO 2:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos2:4\">AMO 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos2:6\">AMO 2:6</a></p>\n<h2>Other examples of the climactic pattern</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job5:19\">JOB 5:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:16-Prov6:19\">PRO 6:16–6:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen4:24\">GEN 4:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl11:2\">ECC 11:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic5:5\">MIC 5:5</a></p>\n<h2>Comparative use of multiples of ten</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:3\">AMO 5:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:8\">LEV 26:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:17\">DEU 33:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg20:10\">JDG 20:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic6:7\">MIC 6:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:7\">LUK 16:7</a></p>\n<h2>Numerical contrast between Saul and David</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:7-1Sam18:8\">1SA 18:7–18:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam21:11\">1SA 21:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam29:5\">1SA 29:5</a></p>",
